{"ts": "2026-06-09T16:41:34.651646+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I have all the information needed. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## How to Run This React Admin App Locally\n\n### Prerequisites\n- **Node.js** (LTS recommended — the Dockerfile uses `node:lts-alpine`)\n- **Yarn** (a `yarn.lock` is committed)\n- Optionally, [**Taskfile**](https://taskfile.dev) for the convenience `task init` shortcut\n\n### Quick-start (local development)\n\n```bash\n# 1. Install dependencies and copy the local env file to the project root\nyarn install\ncp envs/.env.local .env   # or: task init (does both steps plus global tool installs)\n\n# 2. Start the Vite dev server (hot-reload, listens on all interfaces via --host)\nyarn dev\n```\n\n`yarn dev` sets `NODE_ENV=local`, which causes Vite to load `envs/.env.local` (see `vite.config.ts`). The dev server port comes from the `VITE_PORT` variable defined in that env file.\n\n---\n\n## Environment-Specific Commands\n\nThe project supports three environments, each with its own `.env` file in the `envs/` directory:\n\n| Environment | Env file | Dev command | Build command | Vite `--mode` |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Local** | `envs/.env.local` | `yarn dev` | `yarn build` | `prod` |\n| **Staging** | `envs/.env.stg` | `yarn dev:stg` | `yarn build:stg` | `test` |\n| **Production** | `envs/.env.prod` | *(no dedicated dev script)* | `yarn build:prod` | `production` |\n\n### Building\n\n```bash\nyarn build           # production build (mode=prod)\nyarn build:stg       # staging build (mode=test)\nyarn build:prod      # production build (mode=production)\n```\n\nAll builds output to the `dist/` folder (Vite default).\n\n### Previewing a production build locally\n\n```bash\nyarn serve           # runs: vite preview --host\n```\n\nThis serves the contents of `dist/` on a local HTTP server so you can verify the production bundle before deploying.\n\n---\n\n## Deployment Options\n\n### 1. GitHub Pages\n\n```bash\nyarn deploy          # runs: gh-pages -d dist\n```\n\nPushes the `dist/` folder to the `gh-pages` branch. The `homepage` in `package.json` is set to `https://reactZone.github.io/vite-react-ts-admin`.\n\n### 2. Netlify\n\nA `netlify.toml` is included with a SPA redirect rule (`/* → /index.html`, status 200). Connect the repo to Netlify and point the build command to `yarn build:prod`.\n\n### 3. Docker / Nginx\n\n```bash\ndocker build -t vite-react-ts-admin .\ndocker run -p 80:80 vite-react-ts-admin\n```\n\nThe multi-stage `Dockerfile`:\n1. **Builder stage** — installs deps and runs `yarn build` in a Node LTS Alpine image.\n2. **Runtime stage** — copies `dist/` into an Nginx Alpine image and applies the custom `nginx.conf`, which handles SPA routing (including an `/admin` sub-path alias). The container exposes port **80**.\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variable Loading (how it works)\n\n`vite.config.ts` uses `dotenv` and resolves env files in this order:\n\n1. If a `.env` file exists at the project root → load it.\n2. Otherwise → load `envs/.env.${NODE_ENV}` (e.g., `.env.local`, `.env.stg`, `.env.prod`).\n\nThe `task init` command in `Taskfile.yaml` copies `envs/.env.local` to `.env` as a convenience for first-time setup.\n\n---\n\n## Reference: Complete `package.json` Scripts\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"cross-env NODE_ENV=local vite --host\",\n    \"dev:stg\": \"cross-env NODE_ENV=stg vite\",\n    \"serve\": \"vite preview --host\",\n    \"build\": \"vite build --mode prod\",\n    \"build:stg\": \"cross-env vite build --mode test\",\n    \"build:prod\": \"cross-env vite build --mode production\",\n    \"deploy\": \"gh-pages -d dist\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint --ext .jsx,.js,.ts,.tsx .\",\n    \"fix\": \"yarn lint --fix\"\n  }\n}\n```", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1533, "prompt_tokens": 13634, "total_tokens": 15167, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 532, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 12544}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "7a1d770976ff4b8b92ebe615045c491b", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead42-1f0b-7a33-a4b8-a44f2b30bc1d-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 13634, "output_tokens": 1533, "total_tokens": 15167, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 12544}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 532}}}}]}}}
